# 1. 修学旅行と百鬼夜行

Rui: So, I'd like to see if it'll work in our show. What do you think?
Tsukasa: O-Okay...? Limbo in a bamboo forest...? Yes, I agree that it goes with this particular scene, but it's also starting to turn into some sort of comedic skit...
Tsukasa: What?! Look at the time! Our lunch break's almost over!
Rui: Yes, we should start heading back. If I remember correctly, next is...
Tsukasa: A long homeroom. All classes will be having a discussion about the school trip.
Rui: Oh, you already know what's going to happen?
Tsukasa: Heh heh heh! I am a class representative after all! The teachers told me the other day about how we'd be doing this soon!
Rui: Ah, I see. That makes sense.
Rui: Still, the school trip... I hope this discussion doesn't take too long.
Tsukasa: I thought you'd be looking forward to it more.
Rui: Well... I am in the sense that we get to go somewhere that we normally don't...
Rui: But people don't usually like it when I try to put on a show during a school trip. I've even been scolded before for just making a few props in the hotel.
Tsukasa: I had a feeling in the back of my mind, but you really are a creature of habit...
Tsukasa: I appreciate the fact that you love putting on shows wherever and whenever, but why not try doing something else for a change?
Tsukasa: You only get one chance in life as a high schooler to go on this trip! It's like a one-night-only performance!
Rui: Hmm... Like a one-night-only performance...
Tsukasa: Precisely! So, I think you should enjoy this trip as—
Tsukasa: What?! Rui, we need to go now or we're going to be late!
Rui: Okay.
Rui: (Still...)
Rui: (Enjoying the school trip... I did have fun when I participated in the sports festival...)
Rui: (But I'm less sure about this.)
Class Representative: That concludes our overview.
Rui: (Ah, three days and two nights in Kyoto...)
Rui: (Days one and three involve sightseeing with our groups, while we have day two to ourselves. That seems fairly standard...)
Class Representative: We will now be forming our groups. We're free to choose whoever, but we're limited to groups of four.
Rui: (Groups of four...)
Rui: (Based on the explanation we just heard, we'll be doing most things with our groupmates, including sleeping in the same room.)
Rui: (Which means...)
Male Student A: Alright, we're all set!
Male Student B: Yeah, the gang's all here!
Female Student A: Can't we have a group of five...?
Female Student B: Or could we split into a two and a three? Oh, wanna ask the class rep to see if we can have a group of five?
Rui: (Everyone already seems to know who they want to group with...)
Rui: (I've been able to talk to more of my classmates since the sports festival, but I'm not sure who'd want me in their group for this trip...)
???: Hey, uh... Kamishiro, do you have a minute?
Rui: Hm? Oh, you're...
Miyake: It's Miyake! I helped with the equipment during the sports festival... But enough of that. I'm here to ask...
Miyake: Do you wanna join our group?
Rui: What?
Miyake: W-Wait, uhh...! I'm sorry! I know I probably seem like a complete stranger to you.
Rui: No, it's not that... But... Why me?
Miyake: Actually, I've been meaning to chat with you for a while now.
Rui: With me...?
Miyake: Yeah, 'cause I like gadgets and stuff too. The drones you make are so cool.
Miyake: But I sorta never got the opportunity until now, you know? That's why I thought I should take this chance to get to know you better.
Miyake: Also, there are two others already besides me. Hayashi and Taniyama are their names, over there by the wall. You'd be our fourth!
Rui: Ah, are you talking about those two...?
Hayashi: Hey, he's looking this way... I guess Miyake's having trouble getting Kamishiro to join us...
Taniyama: Does this mean he needs backup?! If so, I'll go help!
Rui: They certainly seem like a fun bunch.
Miyake: H-Haha. Sorry, I know this is all happening really suddenly... It's also probably pretty obvious that I'm not exactly the outgoing type, so... I-If you don't want to join us, we'll understand!
Miyake: But it would be nice to have you in our group, Kamishiro...!
Rui: No, I appreciate the invitation.
Rui: Which is why I'd be more than happy to join.
Miyake: R-Really...?! Thanks so much!!
Miyake: Hey, guys! Kamishiro said he'd join!
Rui: (I didn't think that anyone would invite me...)
Rui: (Hehe... This feels so strange for some reason.)
Tsukasa: Ah, Rui! Is your class all finished?
Rui: Hello, Tsukasa. Thank you for waiting. Now, let's head over to the Wonder Stage and...
Rui: Hm? Where's Nene?
Tsukasa: Oh, she just sent me a message saying that we should go on ahead without her because her teacher asked for her help with something.
Tsukasa: More importantly, how did that discussion go with your class? In our class, we decided our groups already...
Rui: Yes, so did we.
Rui: To my surprise, a classmate asked me to join his group. He said he wanted to take this opportunity to get to know me better.
Tsukasa: Wh-What?! Really?!
Rui: Hm? Why so surprised...?
Tsukasa: N-No, it's just...!
Tsukasa: You're apparently known as the “Explosive Mad Scientist” to some people, so I wasn't sure if anyone would invite you into their group...
Rui: Oh, that's not a very nice nickname... I'm just a humble director.
Tsukasa: Um, I'm not sure a “humble director” would run so many experiments at school that end in explosions...
Tsukasa: Still, Rui, congratulations! I hope you and your new friends have a fun trip!
Rui: I don't want to raise my expectations too high, but I am sort of looking forward to spending time with them.
Tsukasa: Yes, excellent!
Tsukasa: Oh, also. Do you already have plans for the second day? We're free to do whatever we like.
Rui: The second day? No, not yet...
Tsukasa: Ah, then! Why don't we do some sightseeing together?
Tsukasa: We're free to mingle with students from other classes, and there's something I'd like to see with you.
Rui: With me?
Tsukasa: Yes, it's called the “Hyakki Yako Parade”, as in “Night Parade of One Hundred Spirits”. It takes place somewhere a little way away from downtown... Oh, this website has a good explanation.
Tsukasa: You get to watch as people walk in a parade while dressed as monsters and spirits from folklore!
Rui: Interesting... “All are free to participate and dress up.” Yes, this does sound like fun.
Tsukasa: See what I mean?! The costumes some of these people make are unbelievable! Professional designers also usually take part, so I'm sure you'll find some inspiration for our shows!
Rui: Hehe... It's usually me that people have pegged as the show enthusiast, but your fanaticism for shows also seems to know no bounds.
Rui: Anyway, I would very much like to see this parade.
Tsukasa: Wonderful! Then, we'll go see this during day two!
Tsukasa: There's also somewhere else that I'm hoping to visit! We'll need to go there before the parade if we can!
Rui: Oh, where?
Tsukasa: None other than the Kiyomizu Stage!
Rui: Well, Kiyomizu-dera Temple is part of a World Heritage Site after all... But why are you so interested in it...?
Rui: Don't tell me it's because it has “Stage” in the name...
Tsukasa: That's exactly right! It is the duty of a future star such as myself to stand on the biggest stages in the world!
Rui: I'd expect no less from you.
Tsukasa: Exactly! Hah hah hah!
Rui: (Still...)
Rui: (Sightseeing with classmates I don't normally interact with, and seeing that parade with Tsukasa...)
Rui: (This school trip is looking to be more fun than I was initially expecting.)
Shizuku: Hmm...
Shizuku: Students who wish to do the tour of Kiyomizu-dera Temple are supposed to gather here, right, Airi?
Airi: Yeah, this should be the right place.
Airi: It's nice how our school's okay with us joining tours and stuff with students from different classes.
Shizuku: Hehe. I agree.
Airi: And I'm so glad this trip doesn't conflict with work or anything. So, let's try to have as much fun as we... Huh?
Mafuyu: Oh... Hello, Hinomori, Momoi.
Mafuyu: Are you two here for the Kiyomizu-dera Temple tour?
Shizuku: Yes, we are! I'm so glad to see you here, Asahina.
Shizuku: But you're all by yourself. Did your friends choose something else?
Mafuyu: Yes, they went for traditional crafts... Unfortunately, that group reached full capacity, so I decided to drop out. Also, I feel that I should see Kiyomizu-dera Temple at least once during my life.
Shizuku: Oh, I see.
Shizuku: I know...! Why don't we go sightseeing together as a group? What do you think, Airi?
Airi: Yeah! How does that sound, Asahina?
Mafuyu: Then, if you don't mind having me.
Shizuku: Of course! The three of us going on a trip together. I couldn't be happier!
Shizuku: This school trip is going to be so wonderful!
